}

SnowQuay: {
	DisplayName: Snow Viper M16
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Use snowballs as ammunition
		Hold left-click to blow a dense stream of snow at your enemies
		Blowing snow builds up pressure in the packing chamber
		Release left-click with enough pressure to launch a packed snowball shell
		"Winter's joy begins with a snowblower"
		'''
}

NeutronGlaive: {
	DisplayName: Black Zone Cleaver
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Swinging releases powerful gravitational sword waves, causing a neutron star explosion upon hitting a target.
		Right-click to charge the blade; releasing it when fully charged triggers a large neutron star explosion at the cursor.
		Releasing before fully charged will cause the energy to spill out.
		'''
}

NeutronBow: {
	DisplayName: Roche's String
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Fires gravity arrows that generate gamma rays upon hitting a target.
		Right-click to perform a three-level charge, releasing three powerful gravity arrows when fully charged.
		'''
	Lang1: Trapping gravity
	Lang2: Is making gravity yield
	Lang3: Finished!!
}

NeutronGun: {
	DisplayName: Stellar Hunter
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Fires gravity projectiles that create warp points upon hitting a target.
		Right-click to switch to sniper mode, firing more powerful gravity bullets that summon gamma rays upon impact.
		Each shot charges the gun, and when fully charged, the next shot triggers a neutron star explosion at the cursor.
		"Shoot the sun down!"
		'''
}

NeutronWand: {
	DisplayName: Light of the Star Tomb
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Fires four powerful gravity stars.
		Right-click to cast gravity magic at the cursor.
		"Legend says that in ancient times, a powerful psychic used this wand to compress stars into black holes,
		but this tale is lost to time, now just a fragment of song sung by interstellar nomads."
		'''
}

NeutronScythe: {
	DisplayName: Blackhole Messenger
	Tooltip:
		'''
		A high-speed spinning neutron scythe that fires gamma rays at nearby enemies and leaves warp detonation points along its path.
		Right click to unleash a Blackhole Burst, hurling thirteen scythes outward in a full circle.
		'''
}

RebelBlade: {
	DisplayName: Rebel Blade
	Tooltip:
		'''
		True melee generates a large number of demon light balls around the target
		Right click to control blade flight and cut towards the cursor
		'''
}

MG42: {
	DisplayName: MG42
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Continuous firing causes the barrel to overheat
		Turning musket bullets into armor-piercing bullets
		'''
}

DragonsWord: {
	DisplayName: Dragon's Word
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Fires dragon tears that spin for a while before homing in on enemies.
		Right-click to cast Dragon Command Magic at the cursor, issuing a death command to enemies within the area.
		"A dragon can shed tears only once in its lifetime."
		'''
}

SnowQuayMK2: {
	DisplayName: Snow Quay MK2
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Use snowballs as ammunition
		A military refit with a cryo-compressor that casts snowballs into high-velocity icicles
		Left-click fires three-round bursts; the final round is a heavy spike that bursts into crystals
		Right-click vents an overpressure scatter of short-ranged icicles
		"The second-generation Snow Viper no longer needs preheating"
		'''
}

JusticeUnveiled: {
	DisplayName: Justice Unveiled
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Ranged attacks build charges of "Judgment Strike", up to a maximum of 5
		Press [UP] to expend 1 charge and call down a devastating holy impact
		"Should justice be summoned, I shall heed the call—wherever it leads."
		'''
}

WeaverGrievances: {
	DisplayName: Weaver Grievances
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Unleash a large number of claws of Evil spirits and have special effects in hell and dungeon environments
		Swings follow a three-hit combo, the third unleashing a sweeping whirlwind finisher
		Right-click and roll in the direction of the cursor as a wheel of vengeful souls. Hitting an enemy during the roll will give the player an invincible frame
		A close roll would be considered a perfect dodge
		[legend]
		'''
	Legend:
		'''
		The eternal dungeon stretches across the land, its walls etched with the inscriptions and screams of ancient warriors. 
		Each stone is saturated with lingering malice, like chains of the damned, binding it to the endless darkness at time’s end.  
		These warriors were once the blades of their king, waging war across the realms. 
		Their swords had illuminated countless battlefields, their blood forged the towering empire. 
		Their loyalty was as enduring as the stars, their conviction as unyielding as iron.  
		Yet, when the wars ceased, and the Demonlord’s banners were torn asunder at the king’s feet, 
		the moment peace descended, the king decreed their consignment to the abyss.  
		“We betrayed not, yet the king has betrayed us!” The anguished wails of the damned tore through the void, piercing the silence of eternity. 
		Their noble spirits did not return to the dust but were imprisoned in the void’s chasm, condemned as witnesses to eternal night.  
		The ceaseless lamentations transformed into a silent accusation, one that reached the furthest ends of the stars.  
		It is said the king, in fear of their unyielding loyalty and the inferno of their wrath, 
		heeded the whispers of the Demonlord’s sorcerers, choosing to consign these warriors to the shadows of history.  
		But malice, like a tide, has twisted the dungeon’s reality. Their suffering has shaken the barriers of time and space, weaving a prophecy of vengeance:  
		“The Demonlord shall return; the void shall be torn asunder, and our wrath shall consume all!”  
		When Terra once more faces the brink of annihilation, these restless dead will rise from the darkness. 
		Their blades will no longer fight for the glory of an empire but for the judgment of the betrayer.  
		Glory and loyalty are long since obliterated—only the flames of vengeance remain, destined to engulf all.
		'''
}

Starship: {
	DisplayName: Starship
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Continuously firing builds heat, increasing fire rate over time
		Right-click to consume ammo and load a comet shell; the next shot fires it for massive damage and inflicts Hyper-Disintegration
		At peak heat, two escort wingmen fly alongside firing homing star bolts; planets are periodically hurled from behind you
		Releasing the trigger unleashes the finale: 14 defense-ignoring homing meteors and a micro-galaxy rain down at the cursor
		'''
}

SandDagger: {
	DisplayName: Sand Dagger
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Hurled in a straight line and lightly pulled down by gravity
		Embeds on impact; if struck into sand, it builds up before bursting upward to unleash a ground shockwave and a volley of sand spikes
		'''
}

UnderTheSand: {
	DisplayName: Beneath the Sand
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Hurls a pair of sand surges that arc downward under gravity
		On impact with the ground, a vertical sand spike erupts from beneath, launching enemies skyward
		'''
}

WastelandFang: {
